				<wikidot:authorName>Kuraden</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2236849</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So, from the description, the shifting lines and widening hole remind me a lot of standard camera focus + aperture function, but functionally taking whoever is 'captured' in the focus chamber into what seems like a dimension in a canvas painting, which is why it forcefully tries to convert anything non-native into canvas.</p> <p>Am I close?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
